function Extracurriculars() { return (

ACM at UCSD

VP Membership

  • Helped change the organization to be more diverse and inclusive by implementing workshops and social events for members to learn about their peers’ unique backgrounds and how to communicate with that in mind
  • Lead the membership team of 6 to organize 30+ social events throughout the year where ACM’s 2000+ members can feel welcome and included

Bit-Byte Director

  • Directed a mentee-mentor program with 100+ participants that helped students create a network and build lasting connections even through the pandemic
  • Hosted and documented 14+ engaging socials, growing and familiarizing the ACM community

The Association for Computing Machinery at UCSD is a student organization founded by Emily Nguyen with a focus on creating a members first community for anyone interested in computing. I joined ACM in 2020 precisely because of this wonderful community and my experience here has greatly shaped my college career. I have had the privilege of being a part of the Membership Team as the bit-byte director for the 2021-2022 school year, and will be continuing in the team as the Vice President of Membership for the 2022-2023 school year!

Peer Listeners

  • Selected out of 300 applicants to be trained in important communication skills such as active listening, mediation, and body language
  • Practiced communication in group sessions of 10 - 20 peers to discuss and improve mental health
  • Helped organize and execute Positive Post-it week where 1000+ positive and encouraging messages were put up around campus

The TCHS Peer Listeners program was established to create a safe space where students can communicate their feelings freely. It is an innovative program where students learn to help each other with their mental and emotional health. I was fortunate enough to be picked to be a part of this program as a Peer Listener, and be trained to help other students with their stresses. I was taught to actively listen, to ask questions for clarification as well as to show that I understand, and how to mediate conflicts. I’m glad that I was a part of the program and learned these important skills that I find myself using everyday, in every conversation. It has helped me understand others and become a more kind, and thoughtful person.

) } export default Extracurriculars;
